HEADWORD: Apodes
<hw>Ap"o*des</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., masc.
pl. See <er>Apoda</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An
order of fishes without ventral fins, including the eels.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A group of holothurians destitute of suckers. See
<er>Apneumona</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apodictic</ent>⟦br⟧
